Here's an example of Actian 4GL code that inserts a new record into the employees table, then commits the change:

```sql
insert into employees(salary, age) values(:new_salary, :new_age);
commit work;
```

The following event block gives the user a choice to commit or roll back changes before the frame closes:
```sql
on terminate = begin
    if CurFrame.ConfirmPopup(messagetext =
        'Commit database changes?') = PU_OK then
        commit work;
    else
        rollback work;
    endif;
end
```
